svrLSMpy Report for Dynamic Emotion Recognition

Methodology

This report is an analysis of the relationship between lesion status and the behavioral score Dynamic Emotion Recognition; performing lesion-symptom mapping using support vector regression. 108 binary lesion files in MNI space were analyzed, including only voxels with at least 10 overlapping lesions. Lesion volume was controlled using vector normalization. Covariates were regressed out of the behavioural scores. Support Vector Regression (SVR) was applied with parameters gamma = 1, cost = 10, and epsilon = 0.1, employing grid search optimization. Z maps were derived from on null distributions based on 1 permutations. Z maps were FDR-corrected for significance at alpha = 0.05. The analysis was completed within -1HRS 52MIN 52SEC.

  • Number of permutations: 1
  • Alpha level: 0.05
